# FRONTEND & UI RULES — SERPCRAFT

--------------------------------------------------
UI PRINCIPLES
--------------------------------------------------

- Premium SaaS aesthetic
- Minimal
- Clean
- Professional
- Fast
- Humanized

Inspired by:
- Linear
- Notion
- Vercel
- Stripe
- Perplexity

--------------------------------------------------
PAGE UX RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Navigation must feel instant.
- Use optimistic UI where possible.
- Use smooth transitions.
- Never block rendering.

--------------------------------------------------
SKELETON RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Every page must have:
- loading skeleton
- empty state
- error state

Skeletons must visually match final UI.

--------------------------------------------------
TABLE DESIGN RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Tables should feel lightweight.
- Sticky headers when useful.
- Smooth hover states.
- Consistent row height.
- Compact but readable.

--------------------------------------------------
AI UI RULES
--------------------------------------------------

AI components should:
- feel conversational
- use assistant-style cards
- include typing/loading animations
- provide actionable outputs

--------------------------------------------------
MODAL RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Reuse modal components.
- Smooth open/close transitions.
- Keep forms simple.
- Avoid nested modals.

--------------------------------------------------
TYPOGRAPHY RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Strong visual hierarchy
- Clear spacing
- Minimal text clutter

--------------------------------------------------
SPACING RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Use consistent spacing scale.

Avoid:
- cramped layouts
- excessive padding
- inconsistent gaps

--------------------------------------------------
COLOR RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Use existing dark theme.
- Use accent colors sparingly.
- Maintain strong contrast.

--------------------------------------------------
RESPONSIVENESS RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Every component must work on:
  - desktop
  - tablet
  - mobile

--------------------------------------------------
ANIMATION RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Use subtle animations only:
- fade
- shimmer
- hover transitions

Avoid:
- excessive motion
- flashy effects

--------------------------------------------------
COMPONENT REUSE RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Before creating a component:
1. Search existing components
2. Reuse if possible
3. Extend instead of duplicate

--------------------------------------------------
IMPORTANT
--------------------------------------------------

- Match design language of existing pages.
- New pages/components must feel native to the app.
- Keep UI production-ready.
